The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 19: The Lok Sabha on Monday passed the bill to cut central sales tax (CST) by 1 per cent from April this year while the Rajya Sabha cleared the appropriation bill to complete the first phase of the ongoing budgetary exercise. The reduction in CST is part of the governments initiative to phase out the tax and merge some central and state levies into a single goods and services tax (GST) by 2010. 

 New Delhi, March 19: Vodafones proposal to acquire 52 per cent controlling stake in Hutchison Essar is expected to be taken up by the Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB) tomorrow. Vodafone had applied for the FIPB clearance on February 22 through Vodafone International Holdings BV, Netherlands. 

 New Delhi, March 19: International long distance calls (isd) may get cheaper as telecom regulator Trai is planning to reduce the levy on both outgoing and incoming isd calls from April 1.

 Mumbai, March 19: The countrys first gold etf Gold Benchmark Exchange Traded Scheme today listed at Rs 1,000 per unit on the National Stock Exchange. 

 Kakinada, March 19: Reliance Industries will invest more than $9 billion to develop a gas field off the east coast of India and build pipelines to sell the fuel to consumers.




